THE diocese of Saint David’s contains the entire counties of Pembroke, Cardigan, Carmarthen, and Brecknock, and all Radnorshire, except six parishes belonging to Hereford. It has also about a fourth part of Glamorganshire; eleven churches and chapels in the county of Hereford, two in Montgomery, and three in Moumouth ¹. It is divided into four archdeaconries; viz.
